com.interpss.core.net.childnet

Interface ChildNetworkWrapper<TBus extends Bus,TBranch extends Branch>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, NameTag, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChildNetworkWrapperImpl

    public interface ChildNetworkWrapper<TBus extends Bus,TBranch extends Branch>
extends NameTag
    A representation of the model object 'Child Network'. It has a reference to a (child) network, a parant network, and a set of interface buses or branches, defining the parnet-child relationship.
    There are two ways to define a parent/child network relationship:
    1) Merge: Parent net and child net are two independent networks. A set of interface buses or branches are used to define parent/child net interface relationship. In essence, a bus in the parent net is linked to a bus in the child net. The parent net bus and the child net bus might have different bus ids.
    2) Split: Starting from one network, parent net and child net(s) are created by network split. the parent/child relationship is defined by a set of interface branches in the original network.

    The following features are supported:

    • Interface Type
    • Network
    • Parent Network
    • Child Net Interfaces
    See Also:
